# Sample Notebook

This is an example of a notebook.

```{js}
document.querySelector('#el').addEventListener('click', () => {
    document.querySelector('#outp').textContent += 'Hello';
});
```
```+html
<button id="el">Click me</button>
<div id="outp"></div>
```
```+test
assert('#el').click().run('Failed to click button', 'Clicked button');
assert('#outp').should('have.text', 'Hello').run('Failed to set output', 'Set output');
```
```html id=blahblah
<html>
  <body>
    <h1>Hello</h1>
  </body>
</html>
```
```{html}
<h1 style="color: blue">Hello</h1>
<button>Click me</button>
```
```+test
assert('h1').should('exist').run('Failed; could not find h1 element', 'Created h1 element');
```
```+css
h1 {
  color: blue;
}
```
```+test
assert('h1').should('exist').should('have.css', 'color: blue').run('Failed to find blue h1 rule', 'Found blue h1 rule');
```

